PTO Cranking Path Test means the performance test for demonstrating the capability of the Black Start Service to energize an isolated cranking path and power up the start-up loads of a target generator in accordance with the CAISO instruction. The PTO Cranking Path performance test shall occur after the Commencement Date.
RA Transactions shall mean any Resource Adequacy Transactions Black Start Generator has entered into for the sale of capacity prior to the execution date of this Agreement.
Reasonable Efforts shall mean with respect to an action required to be taken by a Party, efforts that are timely and consistent with Good Utility Practice and are otherwise substantially equivalent to those a Party would use to protect its own interest.
Recovery Period shall have the meaning defined in Section 3.1.1
Required Regulatory Approvals shall mean any approvals, permits, licenses or amendments thereto from the South Coast Air Quality Management District, California Energy Commission, CAISO, PTO, and the United States Environmental Protection Agency required to provide Black Start Service.
Variable Black Start Payment shall mean the rate determined as set forth in Section 5 of Schedule 5.
Variable Black Start Service Costs shall include the costs identified in Section 3.1.2.
1.3 Rules of Interpretation. The following rules of interpretation and conventions shall apply to this Agreement:
a) if there is any inconsistency between this Agreement and the CAISO Tariff, the CAISO Tariff will only prevail to the extent there is any inconsistency between this Agreement and the CAISO Tariff and the requirements under Article 8 (Monitoring) or Article 9 (Dispute Resolution). This Agreement will prevail to the extent of any other inconsistencies with the CAISO Tariff;
b) the singular shall include the plural and vice versa;
c) the masculine shall include the feminine and neutral and vice versa;
d) includes or including shall mean including without limitation;
e) references to a Section, Article or Schedule shall mean a Section, Article or Schedule of this Agreement, as the case may be, unless the context otherwise requires;
f) a reference to a given agreement or instrument shall be a reference to that agreement or instrument as modified, amended, supplemented or restated through the date as of which such reference is made;
g) unless the context otherwise requires, references to any law shall be deemed references to such law as it may be amended, replaced or restated from time to time;
h) unless the context otherwise requires, any reference to a person includes any individual, partnership, firm, company, corporation, joint venture, trust, association, organization or other entity, in each case whether or not having separate legal personality;
i) unless the context otherwise requires, any reference to a Party includes a reference to its permitted successors and assigns;
j) any reference to a day, week, month or year is to a calendar day, week, month or year; and
k) the captions and headings in this Agreement are inserted solely to facilitate reference and shall have no bearing upon the interpretation of any of the terms and conditions of this Agreement.
ARTICLE 2: TERM AND TERMINATION
2.1 Term. This Agreement will become effective when the Agreement is accepted for filing and made effective by FERC (the Effective Date). If any material modification or condition is ordered by FERC that is unacceptable to a Party, such Party shall communicate its lack of consent to such modification or condition to the other Parties within ten (10) business days after the date on which FERC issued its order, and the Parties shall use best efforts to negotiate mutually acceptable revisions to this Agreement to address the modification or condition. In the event the Parties are unable to negotiate mutually acceptable revisions to this Agreement to address a modification or condition ordered by FERC within sixty (60) business days after the date on which FERC issued its order, the Parties agree to participate in voluntary mediation to attempt to resolve the matter, with the mediator being mutually agreed upon by the Parties. The Black Start Generator shall file with the FERC the Agreement as modified through dispute resolution. Upon the occurrence of the Effective Date, this Agreement shall, subject to Section 2.2 and 2.3, remain in full force and effect for 10 (ten) years following the Commencement Date, or to the later date of extension as set forth in Section 2.2 (Expiry Date).
2.2 Extension. The CAISO may at its sole option and unilaterally, upon giving written notice to Black Start Generator at least one hundred eighty (180) calendar days prior to the Expiry Date, elect to extend the term of this Agreement for a period of time not to exceed five (5) years. In addition, no later than eighteen (18) months prior to the Expiry Date, CAISO will meet with the Black Start Generator and the PTO to discuss the potential for CAISO to extend the term of the Agreement, at which point in time CAISO will provide Black Start Generator and the PTO with a non-binding indication of interest (IOI) regarding (i) CAISOs intention to extend, and (ii) the period of time for which it intends to extend, not to exceed five (5) years. In the event that the CAISO elects to extend the term of this Agreement, the Parties shall negotiate in good faith modifications to this Agreement, and no later than the Expiry Date, the Black Start Generator shall file with the FERC to include in rates the additional costs necessary to provide Black Start Service during the extended term. However, if the Parties are not able to reach agreement on the Fixed Black Start Service Costs and Variable Black Start Service Costs applicable to any such extended term or modifications to this Agreement, and the CAISO and PTO provide written approval to the Black Start Generator to make a filing at FERC to extend the Agreement, the Black Start Generator will file its proposed rates and proposed modifications to this Agreement with FERC pursuant to Section 205 of the FPA. Such costs shall include any additional Fixed Black Start Service Costs and Variable Black Start Service Costs, provided, however, Black Start Generator agrees those costs will reflect the fully depreciated value of the Capital Investment Cost of Black Start Equipment and will not seek further return on or return of the Black Start Equipment Capital Investment Cost. The Black Start Generator may include the value of any additional Black Start Equipment Capital Investment Cost required for such Extension in its proposed costs. Such extension shall not limit or affect in any way the rights of any Party to terminate this Agreement in accordance with Section 2.3.
2.3 Termination
2.3.1 Termination by CAISO and PTO due to Default under this Agreement. The CAISO or the PTO may terminate this Agreement by giving written notice of termination to the Black Start Generator, if the Black Start Generator Defaults under this Agreement, which if capable of being remedied, is not remedied within the time provided under this Agreement after the CAISO or the PTO has given the Black Start Generator written notice of Default, unless excused by reason of Uncontrollable Force in accordance with Section 14 of the CAISO Tariff. With respect to any termination pursuant to this Section, the Black Start Generator will file and the CAISO or the PTO will support a timely notice of termination with the FERC. This Agreement shall terminate upon acceptance by the FERC of such a notice of termination. Termination of this Agreement pursuant to this Section 2.3.1 shall be without prejudice to the right of any Party to collect any amounts due to it prior to the time of termination. If the CAISO or the PTO terminates this Agreement as to any Black Start Unit(s) due to the Black Start Generators Default, the Black Start Generator will not have the right to seek recovery of unamortized costs outlined in Section 3.1.1 for those Black Start Unit(s).
2.3.2 Termination by CAISO or the PTO on Notice. The CAISO or the PTO may terminate this Agreement by giving one (1) calendar year written notice to the Parties. With respect to any notice of termination given pursuant to this section, the Black Start Generator will file and the CAISO or the PTO will support a timely notice of termination with the FERC. In such event, the Black Start Generator shall be entitled to full recovery of unamortized costs outlined in Section 3.1.1, unless the termination was the result of the Black Start Generators Default under this Agreement, in which case Section 2.3.1 shall apply. This Agreement shall terminate upon the effective date determined by FERC after acceptance of such a notice of termination. Termination of this Agreement pursuant to this Section 2.3.2 shall be without prejudice to the right of either Party to collect any amounts due to it prior to the time of termination.
2.3.3 Petition to Terminate by Black Start Generator. Without limiting the provisions of Section 2.3.6, the Black Start Generator may petition the CAISO and the PTO to terminate this Agreement by giving written notice to the CAISO and the PTO at least one (1) calendar year prior to the Expiry Date. Such termination shall take effect on the date accepted for filing and made effective by the FERC. With respect to any termination pursuant to this section, the Black Start Generator will file a timely notice of termination with the FERC; the CAISO and the PTO reserve the right to take any position or no position on such notice. Termination of this Agreement pursuant to this Section 2.3.3 shall be without prejudice to the right of any Party to collect any amounts due to it prior to the time of termination. The Black Start Generator will not have the right to seek recovery of unamortized costs outlined in Section 3.1.1 for those Black Start Unit(s) due to termination under Section 2.3.3 of this Agreement.
2.3.4 Termination by Black Start Generator on Sale of Black Start Generating Unit. The Black Start Generator may terminate this Agreement in relation to a Black Start Generating Unit if it sells the Black Start Generating Unit(s) to a purchaser who, if the CAISO and the PTO requires such unit(s) to continue to provide Black Start Service:
a) executes a Black Start Agreement with the CAISO and the PTO, and files cost of service based rates accepted by the FERC, CAISO and PTO, to provide the CAISO and the PTO with Black Start Service from the Black Start Generating Unit; and
b) satisfies the CAISOs and the PTOs reasonable requirements as to the technical and financial ability of the purchaser to meet its obligations under the contract or rate schedule, as the case may be.
The Black Start Generator will provide one (1) calendar year written notice to the CAISO and the PTO prior to the sale of the Black Start Generating Unit. The Black Start Generator will file and the CAISO and the PTO will support a timely notice of termination with the FERC. This Agreement shall terminate upon acceptance by the FERC of such a notice of termination. Termination of this Agreement pursuant to this Section 2.3.4 shall be without prejudice to the right of any Party to collect any amounts due to it prior to the time of termination. The Black Start Generator will not have the right to seek recovery of unamortized costs outlined in Section 3.1.1 for those Black Start Unit(s) due to termination under Section 2.3.4 of this Agreement.
2.3.5 Termination by Black Start Generator on Modification to Authorization. The Black Start Generator may terminate this Agreement in relation to a Black Start Generating Unit by providing six (6) months written notice to the CAISO and the PTO, if the Black Start Generators authorization from a governmental authority (including, where applicable, licenses under Part I of the Federal Power Act), that is necessary to site, operate or obtain access to that Black Start Generating Unit, is terminated or expires or is reissued or modified so that it becomes illegal, uneconomical or otherwise impractical for the Black Start Generator to continue operating the Black Start Generating Unit. Black Start Generator shall be obligated to use Reasonable Efforts to renew and keep effective its licenses and authorizations and to oppose conditions or modifications which would make continued operation illegal, uneconomical or otherwise impractical; and provided that Black Start Generator requests authorization from the CAISO and the PTO to retire the Power Plant. The Black Start Generator will file and the CAISO and the PTO will support a timely notice of termination with the FERC. This Agreement shall terminate upon acceptance by the FERC of such a notice of termination. Termination of this Agreement pursuant to this Section 2.3.5 shall be without prejudice to the right of any Party to collect any amounts due to it prior to the time of termination. The Black Start Generator will not have the right to seek recovery of unamortized costs outlined in Section 3.1.1 for those Black Start Unit(s) due to termination under Section 2.3.5 of this Agreement.
2.3.6 Termination by Black Start Generator on Retirement of Black Start Generating Unit. If the Black Start Generator requests from the CAISO and the PTO, and the CAISO and the PTO concur on the retirement of the Black Start Generating Unit under the current rules and procedures of the CAISO and the PTO, such that the Black Start Generator can no longer provide Black Start Service under this Agreement, the Black Start Generator may terminate this Agreement in relation to the Black Start Generating Unit by giving six (6) months written notice to the CAISO and the PTO. With respect to any termination pursuant to this section, the Black Start Generator will file and the CAISO and the PTO will support a timely notice of termination with the FERC. This Agreement shall terminate upon the later of the end of the termination notice period or acceptance by the FERC of such a notice of termination. Termination of this Agreement pursuant to this Section 2.3.6 shall be without prejudice to the right of Black Start Generator or CAISO and the PTO to collect any amounts due to it prior to the time of termination. The Black Start Generator will not have the right to seek recovery of unamortized costs outlined in Section 3.1.1 for those Black Start Unit(s) due to termination under Section 2.3.6 of this Agreement.
2.3.7 Termination for Uncontrollable Forces.
a) In the event an Uncontrollable Force, as defined in Section 14 of the CAISO Tariff, prevents a Party from performing its obligations under this Agreement and such inability is estimated to last for a continuous period of six (6) months, upon notice of such Uncontrollable Force, the Parties shall meet and confer within sixty (60) days using good faith Reasonable Efforts to mutually agree on a remediation plan. If the Parties are unable to agree on such remediation plan within such sixty (60) day period, then any Party may terminate this Agreement. The Black Start Generator shall first seek recovery for any unamortized Capital Investment Costs from insurance coverage. The Black Start Generator shall be entitled to recovery of fifty percent (50%) of unamortized Capital Investment Costs as outlined in Section 3.1.1 less insurance recovery and less any salvage costs. The remediation plan will include details of all remediation steps, including scope, schedule, and steps to reinstate Black Start Capability under this Black Start Agreement.
b) If the Parties agree on a remediation plan, but the Black Start Generator fails to use Reasonable Efforts to implement such a remediation plan and fails to cure such failure after thirty (30) calendar days written notice from the CAISO or the PTO, then the CAISO or the PTO may terminate this Agreement, and the Black Start Generator shall not be entitled to recovery of any unamortized costs in Section 3.1.1.
c) With respect to any notice of termination given pursuant to this section, the Black Start Generator will file and the CAISO and the PTO will support a timely notice of termination with the FERC. This Agreement shall terminate upon acceptance by the FERC of such a notice of termination. Termination of this Agreement pursuant to this Section 2.3.7 shall be without prejudice to the right of Black Start Generator or CAISO and the PTO to collect any amounts due to it prior to the time of termination. In such event, this Agreement shall terminate upon the effective date determined by FERC after acceptance of such a notice of termination.
2.3.8 Termination by Black Start Generator due to Lack of Payment under this Agreement. In the event the Black Start Generator does not receive payment under Section 3.1 of this Agreement, and if this lack of payment is not cured within sixty (60) calendar days after Black Start Generator has given the CAISO and the PTO written notice of such lack of payment, unless excused or extended by reason of Uncontrollable Force in accordance with Section 14 of the CAISO Tariff, Black Start Generator may terminate this Agreement. Termination of this Agreement pursuant to this Section 2.3.8 shall be without prejudice to the right of Black Start Generator or CAISO or the PTO to collect any amounts due prior to the time of termination. The Black Start Generator will have the right to seek recovery of unamortized costs outlined in Section 3.1.1 for those Black Start Unit(s).
ARTICLE 3: COMPENSATION
3.1 Compensation to Black Start Generator. The Black Start Generator will file with the FERC in rates the following categories of incremental costs expected to be incurred for the provision of Black Start Service to the CAISO and the PTO. The filed rates will be reflected in Schedule 5 of this Agreement. Article 3 and Schedule 5 of this Agreement will establish the rate of compensation for the Black Start Generator. Section 11 of the CAISO Tariff, and applicable CAISO Business Practice Manuals will govern the process for billing and payment consistent with the provisions of Article 6 of this Agreement. For avoidance of doubt, the CAISOs liability is limited to amounts it receives from the PTO under this Agreement. The CAISO agrees to use Reasonable Efforts to recover all amounts payable under the CAISOs Tariff from the PTO with respect to Black Start Service provided by Black Start Generator under this Agreement.
3.1.1 Fixed Black Start Service Costs. This shall include the monthly amortized Capital Investment Costs and Fixed O&M costs (together, the Fixed Black Start Service Costs) that the Black Start Generator incurs to be able to provide Black Start Service. Amortization shall occur over a 10-year period from the Commencement Date (Recovery Period). If the Agreement is terminated pursuant to Sections 2.3.2, 2.3.7, or 2.3.8, the Black Start Generator shall be entitled upon termination to receive in one lump sum credit for and consistent with the applicable termination provisions (i) all reasonable, necessary and unavoidable unrecovered Capital Investment Costs incurred as of the date of termination, (ii) any remaining incurred and unrecovered Fixed O&M Costs, and (iii) any outstanding Power Plant Outage Cost Reimbursements associated with Power Plant outages, occurring prior to termination, in accordance with Sections 3.2 and 6.5. Upon termination, the Black Start Generator shall provide information regarding costs to the CAISO and the PTO consistent with information filed with the FERC in support of its revenue requirements, to support any recovery of reasonable, necessary and unavoidable unamortized costs. For the avoidance of doubt, in the event of a termination pursuant to Section 2.3.7, recovery shall be reduced as provided therein.
3.1.2 Variable Black Start Service Costs. This shall include the reasonable incremental operating costs, testing costs, and maintenance costs that can be attributed to supporting Black Start Service from a Black Start Generating Unit when Energy is not delivered to the CAISO Controlled Grid (FSNL Operation), under a Black Start Instruction, which shall be recovered in the Variable Black Start Payment calculated as set forth in Schedule 5.
3.1.3 Testing Costs. Black Start Generator will be credited a Variable Black Start Payment for all costs of the Performance Tests and reasonable initial commissioning costs required to achieve Commencement Date, Performance Tests, table-top drills or exercises conducted under Section 5.2, and any other Performance Tests requested by the CAISO or the PTO under this Agreement (but not any unnecessary tests conducted by Black Start Generator for its own account, including re-testing by Black Start Generator after failing to pass a Performance Test requested by the CAISO or the PTO in order to cure a Default), as set forth on Schedule 5. This variable credit reflects the costs of starting up and operating the Black Start Generating Unit during each Performance Test, including reasonable incremental operating costs, costs of starting up and operating auxiliary equipment, the cost of natural gas (including commodity, transportation costs, and manager costs and fees, provided that those costs are incremental to the costs normally incurred by Black Start Generator in the normal course of its business operations or already allowed for recovery under Fixed Black Start Service Costs), and associated costs and expenses incurred to comply with the California Air Resources Board Cap and Trade Program enacted pursuant to California Assembly Bill 32 (AB 32 Compliance Costs), startup costs and taxes, as further described on Schedule 5, and shall be credited to the Black Start Generator. The Black Start Generator shall be credited all Market Revenues (if any) and other compensation payable under the CAISO Tariff with respect to energy deliveries or recovery of costs of operation during such Performance Tests, in accordance with Section 6.3 of this Agreement.
3.2 Power Plant Outage Costs. Black Start Generator will be credited a variable payment for costs and charges that it incurs and for lost capacity payments and lost revenues from any RA Transactions in connection with outages of the Power Plant and any deemed unavailability of the Power Plant under the RA Transactions (referred to collectively as Power Plant Outages). A Power Plant Outage is limited to the following instances: (i) outages or deemed unavailability for the installation, construction, commissioning, and testing of the Black Start Generating Unit; or (ii) outages or deemed unavailability which result from or are necessary (A) to conduct Performance Tests requested by the CAISO of the Black Start Generating Unit, (B) to maintain the Black Start Generating Unit (including testing) after the Commencement Date, (C) to correct, repair or restore an outage of the Black Start Generating Unit after the Commencement Date, (D) Black Start Operations, (E) to conduct PTO Cranking Path Test, or (F) Black Start Service Preservation, with (B) and (C) not being applicable under circumstances caused due to negligence, lack of Good Utility Practice, or otherwise the fault of the Black Start Generator. Black Start Generator shall use Reasonable Efforts to schedule outages of the Black Start Generating Unit(s) necessary for such installation, construction, commissioning, testing, maintenance or repair of the Black Start Generating Unit(s) during the Approved Maintenance Outage or Forced Outages of the Power Plant. The Black Start Generator shall also use Reasonable Efforts to schedule the applicable outages during periods which are already exempt from RAAIM or any future availability incentive mechanism and Resource Adequacy Substitute Capacity obligations.
(a) The CAISO shall exempt the Black Start Generator from the CAISOs Resource Adequacy Availability Incentive Mechanism (RAAIM) or any future availability incentive mechanism adopted by the CAISO for the duration of any outages associated with (i) Performance Tests, (ii) PTO Cranking Path Tests; or (iii) installation, construction, commissioning, and testing of the Black Start Equipment prior to the Commencement Date, if penalties would have been incurred by the Black Start Generator subject to RA Transactions and Other RA Transactions as a result of such outages. For the duration of such outages, the CAISO shall not require the Black Start Generator to provide Resource Adequacy Substitute Capacity.
(b) Following any such outage or deemed unavailability, Black Start Generator will determine whether its compensation under a RA Transaction has been or will be reduced as a result of a reduction in availability or deemed availability of the Power Plant. If its compensation under the RA Transaction has been or will be reduced as a result of such outage or deemed unavailability or otherwise imposes additional costs and charges, the CAISO will credit Black Start Generator the full amount of the reduction in compensation under the RA Transaction (the Power Plant Outage Cost Reimbursement), not to exceed $250,000 in any single month (the Outage Expense Cap). Black Start Generator shall provide to the CAISO an invoice and supporting documentation reflecting such costs and charges or reductions in compensation under the RA Transaction; provided that if any applicable Power Plant Outage Cost Reimbursement credit with respect to any Power Plant Outage would exceed the Outage Expense Cap, Black Start Generator may petition FERC to recover any such excess costs as provided in Section 3.2(c). Without limiting the generality of the foregoing, to the extent that installation, construction, commissioning, testing, maintenance or repair of the Black Start Generating Unit is performed during an outage of the Power Plant scheduled for other reasons, Power Plant Outage Cost Reimbursement charges will not be credited with respect to such outage unless the outage is extended due to the installation, construction, commissioning, testing, maintenance or repair of the Black Start Unit, in which case Black Start Generator shall be credited the Power Plant Outage Cost Reimbursement based on any reductions in compensation under a RA Transaction for the period of such extension as set forth herein.
(c) In the event the Power Plant Outage Cost Reimbursement payment with respect to any Power Plant Outage would exceed the Outage Expense Cap, the Black Start Generator may file a petition with FERC under Section 205 of the FPA and pursuant to FERC rules and regulations promulgated thereunder to recover such excess costs; provided that, prior to filing a petition under Section 205 of the FPA, the Black Start Generator shall provide the CAISO and PTO a statement of such additional costs. The CAISO and PTO shall notify the Black Start Generator of any objections that such costs were not reasonably incurred within sixty (60) calendar days of receipt. For the avoidance of doubt, Black Start Generator is not required to seek FERC approval of Power Plant Outage Cost Reimbursement payments that do not exceed the Outage Expense Cap for the outage in question. The CAISO and PTO also agree that failure to notify the Black Start Generator of any such objections within such sixty (60) calendar day period shall constitute approval of such additional costs. In the event that Black Start Generator seeks to recover additional costs, the Parties will meet and confer and use Reasonable Efforts to resolve any such objections and agree on the additional costs that Black Start Generator may recover, provided, however, that if the Parties are unable to agree within a reasonable period of time, Black Start Generator shall have the right to unilaterally seek such cost recovery from FERC.
(d) With respect to Other RA Transactions, except as provided below with respect to Power Plant Outages caused by Performance Tests or PTO Cranking Path Tests, Power Plant Outage Costs shall not be eligible for compensation provided in Article 3.2 (b) and (c) of this Agreement, unless (i) the CAISO Tariff has been modified resulting in new replacement RA obligations for transmission outage types that are not subject to such obligations as of the Effective Date, and (ii) the Black Start Generator is unable to modify Other RA Transactions using Reasonable Efforts to prevent the incurrence of Power Plant Outage Costs as a result of this change. If such an event were to occur, the Parties agree to allow Power Plant Outage Costs incurred under Other RA Transactions to be eligible for recovery under Article 3.2.
(e) Performance Tests or PTO Cranking Path Tests that cause Power Plant Outage Costs with respect to Other RA Transactions shall be recoverable by Black Start Generator to the same extent and on the same basis as RA Transactions.
3.3 Market Revenues during Black Start Operation. Following the occurrence of a Black Start Event, once the Black Start Generating Unit is in Energy Delivery Operation, Black Start Generator shall be credited, and shall be entitled to receive, all market revenues and other compensation payable under the CAISO Tariff, including without limitation all settlement credits of Locational Marginal Price, Administrative Prices for energy established by the CAISO, and all Bid Cost Recovery payments for such period (Market Revenues); provided, however, if the Market Revenues credited to Black Start Generator for any period of Energy Delivery Operation are less than the credits that the Black Start Generator would have received pursuant to Schedule 5 for the same period when operating pursuant to a Black Start Instruction (such shortfall being the Market Revenue Shortfall), Black Start Generator shall be credited the Market Revenue Shortfall amount for such period and shall calculate (based on then available information) and include the Market Revenue Shortfall amounts in its invoice for the applicable billing period under Section 6.6. If any payments attributable to these amounts are paid to a person not party to this Agreement or to the PTO, CAISO will cooperate with and assist Black Start Generator in resolving any payment related disputes. If any of the amounts used to compute either Market Revenues or the Market Revenue Shortfall are subsequently revised or resettled by the CAISO, the amounts invoiced by and credited to Black Start Generator will be adjusted as provided in Section 6.6.
ARTICLE 4: BLACK START SERVICE
4.1 Obligation to Complete Black Start Performance Test. Black Start Generator shall complete a Performance Test for all eight (8) Black Start Generating Units, provided however only four (4) of the Black Start Generating Units need to successfully complete the Performance Test to commence service under this Agreement, with all eight (8) Black Start Generating Units being tested periodically as provided in Schedule 7 thereafter. The Performance Test will not be deemed complete or successful unless approved as such by the CAISO and PTO. Any such approval required from the CAISO and the PTO shall not be delayed, conditioned or withheld if the Performance Test was successful in accordance with effective CAISO Tariff provisions, Business Practice Manuals, and Operating Procedures, applicable to the conduct, review, and approval of Performance Tests.
4.2 Obligation to Maintain Black Start Service. From the Commencement Date and until the Expiry Date, the Black Start Generator shall maintain Black Start Service at each of its Black Start Generating Units in an amount no less than that stated for such Black Start Generating Units in Schedule 2. Black Start Service shall be provided only from the Black Start Generating Units listed in Schedule 2 of the Agreement that have successfully completed the Performance Test. Black Start Generator shall be excused from maintaining Black Start Service during any period that Black Start Generating Units are unavailable due to an Approved Maintenance Outage, a Forced Outage or an Uncontrollable Force; provided that (i) the Black Start Generator shall use Reasonable Efforts to remedy the effects of such Forced Outage or Uncontrollable Force and to restore the availability of the Black Start Generating Unit as quickly as reasonably possible, and (ii) Black Start Generator shall not be excused from maintaining Black Start Service if an outage occurred as a direct result of Black Start Generators failure to maintain its Black Start Generating Unit(s) consistent with Good Utility Practice or as needed to be able to operate in accordance with the terms of this Agreement, all existing and effective CAISO Tariff provisions, including any applicable Appendices thereto, Business Practice Manuals, and Operating Procedures pertaining to Black Start Service.
4.3 Specific Obligations. The Black Start Generator shall from the Commencement Date and thereafter until the Expiry Date, consistent with the requirements of this Agreement, provide and maintain at each Black Start Generating Unit all necessary supplies, water, consumables, and equipment, and shall maintain all necessary communication systems, have in place all necessary valid permits, licenses, procedures and provide all necessary staff training and shall maintain the Black Start Equipment in a continuous state of readiness provided, however, that the Black Start Generator shall not be required to maintain the Black Start Equipment in a continuous state of readiness in the event of an Approved Maintenance Outage or a Forced Outage. When reasonably directed to do so by the CAISO or the PTO, the Black Start Generator shall participate in CAISO and PTO table-top drills or exercises. From the Commencement Date until the Expiry Date, the Black Start Generating Unit shall comply with Applicable Reliability Criteria. Upon the Expiry Date, Black Start Generator shall decommission the batteries and inverters installed as components of the Black Start Equipment. In addition, if this Agreement is not extended as provided in Section 2.2, upon such decommissioning, Black Start Generator shall refund any realized salvage value (net of decommissioning costs) of any Black Start Equipment to the CAISO.
4.4 CAISO Tariff. The Black Start Generator shall comply with the obligations and requirements that are applicable to the provision of Black Start Service set out in the CAISO Tariff. ARTICLE 5: UTILIZATION OF BLACK START
5.1 Black Start Instructions. All Black Start Instructions given by the CAISO or the PTO with respect to Black Start Operations, and those related to Performance Tests, shall, if reasonably possible, be given to the Scheduling Coordinator for the Black Start Generating Unit or to Black Start Generator in accordance with the applicable CAISO Tariff provisions and Operating Procedures; provided that, after the occurrence and during the continuation of a Black Start Event (or an event reasonably believed by Black Start Generator to be a Black Start Event), Black Start Generator may act, and shall be justified in acting, on a Black Start Instruction from either the CAISO or the PTO. The Black Start Generator shall, when it or its Scheduling Coordinator receives a Black Start Instruction from the CAISO, or from the PTO when designated by the CAISO, provide Black Start Service in accordance with the requirements of Schedule 3 and, to the extent not inconsistent with this Agreement, the CAISO Operating Procedures and the Black Start Instruction.
If the Black Start Generator believes that an event which creates a need for Black Start Service has occurred, if it has not already been contacted by the CAISO or PTO, the Black Start Generator shall attempt to contact the CAISO or PTO to verify the need for Black Start Service and to receive dispatch instructions; provided, however, if a Black Start Service Preservation has occurred (or is reasonably believed by Black Start Generator to have occurred), Black Start Generator shall start the Black Start Generating Unit and begin FSNL Operation pending receipt of further dispatch instructions from the CAISO or the PTO. Operation of the Black Start Generating Unit after the Black Start Service Preservation has occurred (or is reasonably believed by Black Start Generator to have occurred) shall be considered to be Black Start Operation pursuant to a Black Start Instruction from the CAISO or the PTO for all purposes under this Agreement, including payment, whether or not a Black Start Event has in fact occurred. In the event the Black Start Generator starts the Black Start Generating Unit in FSNL Operation, it will not energize or attempt to synchronize to the PTO transmission system and CAISO Controlled Grid until it has received instructions to do so from CAISO or the PTO.
5.2 Performance Tests, Table-Top Drills, and Other Exercises. Subject to Schedule 7, the CAISO or the PTO may carry out a Performance Test, table-top drill, or other exercise on a Black Start Generating Unit in accordance with the CAISO Tariff, CAISOs Operating Procedures, and/or PTO Operating Procedures pertaining to Black Start Service.
5.3 Black Start Operation or Performance Test. The Black Start Generator acknowledges that during a Black Start Event its Black Start Generating Units may be asked to operate outside of their normal operational capability, but within emergency operating limits, described in Schedule 2. The CAISO or PTO will not knowingly issue an instruction that requires the Black Start Generating Units to operate at a level in conflict with any equipment limitation that has been provided to the CAISO or PTO and incorporated in Schedule 2 of the Black Start Agreement. Black Start Generator shall comply with such an instruction unless the Black Start Generator believes it is necessary for safety reasons or to maintain compliance with law (whether relating to personnel or plant and/or equipment), or to avoid operation of equipment outside of Schedule 2 parameters. If the CAISO or PTO provides a Black Start Instruction or calls for a Performance Test that would require operation of equipment outside the Schedule 2 parameters that risks damage to the Black Start Generators facilities, the Black Start Generator shall, if time permits, inform the CAISO, or if applicable the PTO, of any such risk and seek confirmation of the relevant instruction. Under no circumstance will the Black Start Generator be subject to penalty pursuant to Section 7.1 due to a Black Start Failure if a CAISO or PTO instruction requires operation outside of the Schedule 2 parameters.
5.4 Black Start Outage Reporting. The Black Start Generator shall notify the CAISO via Outage Management System in accordance with Section 9 of the CAISO Tariff and applicable CAISO Operating Procedures when Black Start Service is not available. In the event that a Forced Outage or an Uncontrollable Force creates a known change to the capabilities of that Black Start Generator to provide Black Start Service, the Black Start Generator shall notify the CAISO and PTO immediately of this change, but in all cases within 24 hours following such change.
5.5 Communication. The Parties shall each operate and maintain a 24-hour, 7-day control center with real-time scheduling and control functions. Appropriate control center staff will be provided by each Party, who shall be responsible for operational communications, and who shall have sufficient authority to commit and bind that Party. The Parties shall jointly develop communication procedures necessary to support scheduling and dispatch functions relative to Black Start Service. The Parties agree to exchange operational contact information in a format to be provided by the CAISO and completed as of the Effective Date of this Agreement or at a later date as requested by either the CAISO or the PTO. Each Party shall provide the other Parties ten (10) days advance notice of updates to its operational contact information for known changes, and as soon as practical, for unplanned changes.
ARTICLE 6: INVOICING, BILLING, AND PAYMENT
6.1 Invoicing, Billing, and Payment for Black Start Service. Invoicing, billing, and payment for Black Start Service will be made pursuant to the procedures described in this Article 6, with CAISO payment of the full amount not to exceed, in any case contemplated by this Agreement, sixty (60) days of receipt by CAISO of the invoice, notice, or adjustment submitted by Black Start Generator. Invoices for Black Start Operations, Performance Tests, and table-top drills or exercises pursuant to Sections 6.3 and 6.4 shall be credited as set forth in those sections; provided, however, that, notwithstanding anything in the CAISO Payment Calendar or the CAISO Tariff to the contrary, except with respect to adjustment of Market Revenues as provided in Section 6.6, such invoices shall only be subject to subsequent adjustment as provided in this Article 6. Except as otherwise provided herein, disputes regarding invoices submitted by Black Start Generator shall be resolved in accordance with Section 13 of the CAISO Tariff. All invoices and supporting documentation must be submitted to the CAISO with a copy to the PTO. The CAISO will act as a primary point of contact for the receipt, review, and response to submitted invoices and supporting documentation, unless specified otherwise by CAISO or the PTO.
6.2 Monthly Payment for Black Start Service. The CAISO shall credit the Black Start Generator for Black Start Service costs described in Schedule 5 on a monthly basis in accordance with Section 11 of the CAISO Tariff. The CAISO will credit the full monthly amount on a Settlement Statement in sufficient time for Black Start Generator to receive payment no later than the last day of the month. This process shall commence in the month following the Commencement Date and all monthly credits under Section 6.2 shall cover the Black Start Service for the preceding month. Any dispute shall be handled in accordance with Section 11 of the CAISO Tariff.
6.3 Payment for Black Start Performance Testing. In the event of a Black Start Instruction for a Performance Test by the CAISO, the Energy provided during a Performance Test from a Black Start Instruction will be settled as provided in Section 11.4 of the CAISO Tariff. The Black Start Generator shall retain any and all payments attributable to the delivery of Energy under this provision. Black Start Generator shall credit any market revenues received under the CAISO Tariff during a Performance Test requested by the CAISO (the Testing Revenue Credit) against amounts that Black Start Generator would otherwise invoice with respect to such Performance Test hereunder. The Testing Revenue Credit as shown on the applicable invoice shall be based on market revenues actually received by Black Start Generator prior to issuance of the invoice and shall be subject to adjustment as provided in Section 6.6. The Black Start Generator shall include in its invoice to the CAISO, no later than thirty (30) calendar days from the occurrence of a Performance Test or at a later date if agreed to by all Parties, Testing Costs payable to the Black Start Generator under Section 3.1.3. These Testing Costs shall be calculated as provided in Section 3.1.3 and shall be treated by the Parties as Black Start Service costs. The Black Start Generator shall provide supporting documentation to the CAISO and PTO for review along with any invoice that includes these Testing Costs associated with a Black Start Instruction for a Performance Test. The CAISO shall credit the Black Start Generator the entire amount specified as Testing Costs associated with a Black Start Instruction for a Performance Test no later than sixty (60) days from the date of submittal as part of a Settlement Statement. If the CAISO does not agree with the amounts invoiced by Black Start Generator, it shall nonetheless credit the full amount of the invoice in the manner described above and shall concurrently give Black Start Generator a written notice describing dispute in reasonable detail. The Parties shall use commercially reasonable efforts to resolve any such dispute within sixty (60) days after making the payment and delivering such notice. If they are unable to do so, the dispute will be resolved in accordance with Section 13 of the CAISO Tariff. Failure to deliver a notice of dispute concurrently with making a payment shall be deemed an acceptance of the amount of the related invoice and a waiver of any dispute related thereto by the CAISO. Following resolution of the dispute, Black Start Generator will submit an adjusted invoice reflecting such resolution, and any necessary adjustments will be made within forty-five (45) days after submission of the adjusted invoice, on a Settlement Statement. Without limiting the foregoing, adjustments may be made by debiting or crediting amounts on other invoices issued by Black Start Generator. Costs incurred during a PTO Cranking Path Test shall be subject to this Section 6.3 for recovery by the Black Start Generator.
6.4 Payment for Black Start Event. The Energy provided during a Black Start Event from a Black Start Instruction will be settled as provided in Section 11.4 of the CAISO Tariff. The Black Start Generator shall include in its invoice to the CAISO, no later than thirty (30) calendar days from the occurrence of a Black Start Event or at a later date agreed to by the Parties, covering amounts under Sections 3.1.2 and 3.3 (if there is a Market Revenue Shortfall). The Variable Black Start Service Costs shall be calculated as per the formula in Schedule 5, Section 5 and shall be treated by the Parties as Black Start Service costs. The Black Start Generator shall provide supporting documentation to the CAISO and PTO for review along with any invoice that includes charges for Variable Black Start Service Costs associated with Black Start Operations. All billing and payments shall be made in accordance with the process described in Section 6.3 of this Agreement.
6.5 Power Plant Outages. The Black Start Generator shall submit an invoice to the CAISO and PTO for Power Plant Cost Reimbursement, calculated as set forth in Section 3.2, no later than the later of (i) thirty (30) days after the completion of any Power Plant outage described in Section 3.2, or (ii) thirty (30) days after receipt of the applicable invoice under an RA Transaction reflecting the costs recoverable under Section 3.2 in connection with such Power Plant outage, or at a later date if agreed to by all Parties, covering amounts payable to Black Start Generator under Section 3.2 (Power Plant Outage Invoice). The Black Start Generator shall provide reasonable supporting documentation to the CAISO and PTO for review along with any invoice that includes these Power Plant Outage Costs. If the CAISO or PTO do not agree with the amounts invoiced by Black Start Generator, the CAISO shall credit the Black Start Generator the entire amount specified as Power Plant Outage Costs no later than sixty (60) days from the date of submittal as part of a Settlement Statement; and shall concurrently give the Black Start Generator a written notice describing any such dispute in reasonable detail. The Parties shall use commercially reasonable efforts to resolve any such dispute within sixty (60) days after making the payment and delivering such notice. If they are unable to do so, the dispute will be resolved in accordance with Section 13 of the CAISO Tariff as provided herein. In all other respects, the Power Plant Outage Invoice submission, settlement and billing shall follow all the requirements and processes described in Section 6.3.
6.6 Adjustment of Market Revenues. Billing and payments of Market Revenues with respect to a Black Start Event or Performance Test will be processed in accordance with Section 11 of the CAISO Tariff, the applicable CAISO BPM and the CAISO Payments Calendar (but in no event later than sixty (60) days from the occurrence of a Black Start Event or Performance Test). If the Market Revenues credited to Black Start Generator with respect to periods of Energy Delivery Operations or the Market Revenues credited to Black Start Generator with respect to transactions entered into in connection with Performance Tests are adjusted in any CAISO settlement subsequent to the settlement on which the invoices under Sections 6.3 or 6.4 were based, the Market Revenue Shortfall or Testing Revenue Credit, as applicable, shall be adjusted to reflect what it would have been, based on the subsequent CAISO settlement, and Black Start Generator shall be paid any additional amounts due or shall be charged for any excess payments, as applicable, no later than sixty (60) days from the time of such adjustment as part of a Settlement Statement. Any such adjustments shall account for all prior settlements and adjustments, if any, so that the net amount (after all adjustments) credited to Black Start Generator equals what it would have been credited, had the revised Market Revenue Shortfall, as applicable, been known at the time the original Settlement Statement was issued.
ARTICLE 7: RELIABILITY-RELATED VIOLATIONS
7.1 Black Start Failure and Penalties. If a Black Start Failure occurs in response to a Black Start Instruction during a Black Start Event and such a Black Start Failure contributes in whole or in part to a reliability-related standard violation for which FERC, the North American Electric Reliability Corporation (NERC), the Western Electricity Coordinating Council (WECC), or any other regulatory body imposes a penalty for reliability-related violations, then the CAISO or the PTO may, consistent with applicable provisions of the CAISO Tariff and this Agreement, and subject to FERC approval, seek to directly allocate, in whole or in part, the cost of any such penalties assessed upon the CAISO or the PTO to the Black Start Generator whose conduct or omission FERC determines contributed, in whole or in part, to the violation that gave rise to the penalty.
ARTICLE 8: MONITORING
8.1 Access to Records and the Facilities. Subject to Section 8.2, the Black Start Generator shall provide, arrange and make available to the CAISO and the PTO such of the following as the CAISO or the PTO may reasonably require, and as is strictly necessary to enable the CAISO and the PTO to monitor and predict Black Start Service and performance of a Black Start Generating Unit:
a) the Black Start Generators relevant records and relevant data relating to all the Black Start Generating Units within the Black Start Generators Black Start facilities including any relevant air quality/emission reports, environmental certifications, operational limits for emissions and related State or local permits;
b) the Black Start Generators relevant records and relevant data relating to auxiliary and Generating Units, gas turbine and startup equipment at the Black Start Generators Black Start facilities;
c) the Black Start Generators relevant records and relevant data relating to the Black Start Generators plant, apparatus, equipment and stocks of all relevant fuels and consumables at the Black Start Generators Black Start facilities; and
d) the Black Start Generators documentation relating to the procedures used at the Black Start Generators Black Start facilities for the provision of Black Start Service.
8.2 Inspection. The CAISO or the PTO shall give the Black Start Generator not less than five (5) business days written notice of the CAISO or the PTOs intent to inspect Black Start facilities and not less than ten (10) business days written notice of the CAISOs or the PTOs request for information in order for the Black Start Generator to provide access to records and data.
8.3 Reports. The Black Start Generator will provide monthly progress reports following the Effective Date up to the Commencement Date. The format and information required in the monthly report shall be agreed upon by all Parties. In addition to the above, annually after the Effective Date, within sixty (60) days after each anniversary of the Effective Date, Black Start Generator shall provide: (i) prior to the Commencement Date, a written report to the CAISO and the PTO accounting for the Capital Investment Costs incurred through such anniversary, with the final such report to be provided to the CAISO and the PTO within sixty (60) days following the Commencement Date, and (ii) subsequent to the Commencement Date, a written report to the CAISO and the PTO of all payments received by Black Start Generator under this Agreement and all third-party Fixed O&M Costs incurred by Black Start Generator through such anniversary date. The CAISO and the PTO acknowledge that such reporting will be used solely for informational, situational awareness, and internal tracking purposes. The CAISO and the PTO affirm that all reports shall be treated as Confidential Information in accordance with Section 14.1. For the avoidance of doubt, the CAISO and the PTO will not use such reports as the basis for re-negotiation or revisions to the rates set forth in the Agreement.
8.4 Coordination between CAISO and PTO. The CAISO and PTO shall use reasonable efforts to coordinate their communications with Black Start Generator so as to avoid conflicting direction and minimize the administrative burden on Black Start Generator. The Parties agree that CAISO should be the primary point of contact as between the CAISO and the PTO with Black Start Generator for the administration of this Agreement. In the case of a Black Start Event, the Parties anticipate that communication will come from the PTO. However, in the event of a conflict or contradictory direction, Black Start Generator shall resolve such conflict in favor of or otherwise follow the direction of the CAISO.
8.5 Modeling, Testing, and Permitting Obligations. Black Start Generator will take the following actions with regard to modeling, testing and permitting:
a) provide detailed equipment data required to model units for Black Start studies and CAISO and PTO NERC compliance studies by deadline specified by CAISO and PTO;
b) work with PTO to plan and execute a PTO Cranking Path Test that energizes a cranking path to a target unit (currently planned as Mountain View Generating Station) to start target unit start-up loads in preparation for startup. This will also require co-operation in installing required temporary metering equipment; and,
c) co-operate with PTO to obtain temporary AQMD waiver, if required, to perform PTO Black Start testing.

Unless otherwise stated, all operational parameters of the Black Start Generating Units will be identical to the values contained in the CAISO Master File for each Resource ID.
Full Speed No Loan Configuration Description:
After a Black Start Generating Unit receives a Black Start Instruction or due to Black Start Service Preservation, the unit will be started and operated at Full Speed No Load (FSNL), at which point the Black Start Generating Unit is available to synchronize to the grid or close into a dead bus configuration. After a Black Start Instruction is received or Black Start Service Preservation, a Black Start Generating Unit will require approximately 12 minutes to reach FSNL when starting from high-speed turning gear, or 10 minutes when on low speed turning gear.

· Must satisfy the NERC definition of Black Start Resource; · Must be able to supply own startup power; · Must serve own plant load; · Must have ability to meet fault impedance requirements of the restoration path. Generator protection relays should be flexible to assume temporary setting changes required to provide adequate protection during anticipated black start system configurations. This could be accommodated, but is not limited to, by utilizing microprocessor based protective relays with multiple group setting capability; · Must follow the CAISO Approved Maintenance Outage procedures; and CAISO Tariff Provisions · Must have ability to meet minimum continuous running time for unit - 48 hours; · Must have ability to energize a dead transmission bus within targeted timeframe of 3 hours; and · Must meet applicable requirements and obligations set under the CAISO Tariff.

Section 5 Variable Black Start Payment. The Variable Black Start Payment for the Black Start Generator both for operation during a Black Start Event, as provided in Sections 3.1.2, and for Performance Tests, as provided in Section 3.1.3, for the Billing Month shall be the amount calculated in accordance with the following formula:
Variable Black Start Payment = (a) the Fuel Charge + (b) the Variable O&M Charge + (c) the Emissions Charge + (d) the Starts Charge + (e) the Battery Energy Charge + (f) CAISO/PTO Charge Reimbursement + (g) Power Plant Outage Cost Reimbursement
Where: Each of the above charges are calculated as described below for the Billing Month in which such payments are applicable.
(a) Fuel Charge = BS Fuel Transportation Fee + i=1nBS Fuel Costsi where, n = the number of days in the applicable month BS Fuel Costi = Black Start Fueli x Gas Index Pricei BS Fuel Transportation Fee = (Black Start Fuel) / (Total Delivered Gas) x Total Gas Transportation Bill
(b) Variable O&M Charge = ($140 /FSNL Hour x CPI x FSNL Hours) + ($5 /MWh x CPI x Black Start MWhs)
where,
FSNL Hours are those hours that a unit is operating at Full Speed No Load and not injecting energy into the CAISO Controlled Grid.
$140 /FSNL Hour is the agreed upon base variable charge for the units when operating at Full Speed No Load since the output of the unit is not able to be measured during FSNL.
$5 / MWh is the agreed upon base variable operations and maintenance fee.
Black Start MWh's are those MWhs that a unit is under load and generating and those hours are not being otherwise compensated under CAISO market settlements in accordance with the CAISO Tariff.
CPI or Consumer Price Index for this Agreement means the value reported on the Bureau of Labor Statistics for West Urban Consumers U.S. All items, 1982-84 = 100.
(c) Emissions Charge = Emission Rate x Black Start Fuel x GHG Rate
where,
The Emission Rate equals 0.0539 MTCO2e per MMBTU, and
The GHG Rate is the Current Auction Settlement Price for the most recent auction as published by the California Air Resources Board under the California Cap-and-Trade Program.
(d) Start-up Charge = $1,200 x CPI x Number of Unit Starts
(e) Battery Energy Charge = (Standby Energy + Black Start Energy x Loss Rate) x Energy Rate
where,
Standby Energy is equal to the amount of metered standby energy used by the batteries during the Billing Month in order to maintain required temperature and warranty conditions.
Black Start Energy is the amount of Battery Energy used during Black Start Events and Black Start Performance Tests.
Energy Rate is equal to the $/MWh rate for TOU8 electrical supply or its successor rate during the Billing Month and calculated by dividing the total TOU8 or its successor rate invoice for the invoice month corresponding to the Billing Month by the total MWhs during the same month.
Loss Rate is the factor used to reflect the round-trip energy losses during charge and discharge cycles and is 1.13636
(f) CAISO/PTO Charge Reimbursement are any charges levied by the CAISO or PTO directly related to the Black Start Event but do not include any grid settlements associated with any exported energy.
(g) Power Plant Outage Cost Reimbursement as set forth in Schedule 6.
Section 6 Investment Tax Credit Treatment. To the extent Black Start Generator seeks and obtains the Investment Tax Credit (ITC) available for the investment in energy storage technology as a result of its installation of Black Start Equipment, Black Start Generator shall seek appropriate adjustment of the Fixed Black Service Costs pursuant to Section 205 of the FPA and pursuant to FERC rules and regulations promulgated thereunder to ensure that the Fixed Black Service Costs accurately reflects the utilization of the ITC.
SCHEDULE 6 POWER PLANT OUTAGE COST REIMBURSEMENT
Power Plant Outage Cost Reimbursement payments to be made by the CAISO under this Agreement shall be determined according to the formula set forth below which the Parties agree represents a fair and reasonable calculation of the verifiable costs incurred by the Black Start Generator under the RA Transactions as the result of a Power Plant Outage.
Power Plant Outage Cost Reimbursement = Normal Monthly RA Transaction Capacity Payments Reduced Monthly RA Transaction Capacity Payment + Replacement RA Capacity Costs + CAISO Charges
Where:
Normal Monthly RA Transaction Capacity Payments = the capacity payment paid by the RA Transaction counterparty or counterparties, as the case may be, for the month in which the Power Plant Outage occurs.
Reduced Monthly RA Transaction Capacity Payment = the reduced capacity payment paid as a result of the Power Plant Outage.
Replacement RA Capacity Costs = the cost of providing substitute RA as a result of a Power Plant Outage.
CAISO Charges include RAIIM Adjustment Penalties, which shall be the share of monthly RAIIM penalties attributable to the Power Plant Outage(s) and calculated by dividing the Power Plant Outage Hours by the total applicable RAIIM Outage Hours and multiplying the result by the RAIIM Penalty in the Billing Month
SCHEDULE 7 PERFORMANCE AND PTO CRANKING PATH TESTING
This Schedule details the frequency and timing of the CAISOs Performance Test and the PTOs Cranking Path Test. CAISO Performance Test: CAISO shall require the conduct of a periodic Performance Test once every three years, counting from the Commencement Date of the Agreement. The four (4) designated Black Start Units shall be tested during these periodic Performance Tests with the other four (4) non-designated Black Start Units tested in alternate years. These Performance Tests are in addition to the following: 1) the Performance Test required to fulfill requirements of the Commencement Date, during which only the four (4) designated Generating Units of the eight (8) Generating Units are required to commence service, and 2) any Performance Tests required by the CAISO to verify the availability of Black Start Service.
PTO Cranking Path Test: PTO expects that it will only conduct a PTO Cranking Path Test once every three years but may conduct up to one such test each year if changes in grid topology makes more frequent testing necessary provided it conducts such tests in conjunction with other Performance Tests. Any such test will be for a maximum duration of eight (8) hours. However, when conducting a PTO Cranking Path Test, PTO may only dispatch two of the four Black Start Units and may not direct the Black Start Unit to operate in FSNL for more than sixty (60) minutes. The PTO Cranking Path Test shall not be conducted during the months of June through October unless the Parties otherwise agree. The Parties will work cooperatively and in good faith to put in place procedures regarding notice and scheduling to minimize adverse impacts of the operations of Black Start Generator commercial arrangements with third parties. CAISO and/or PTO will provide at least ninety (90) days notice to Black Start Generator of any testing event. Neither CAISO nor PTO shall schedule a testing event during an Approved Maintenance Outage or Forced Outage.
